        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-08-16T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-08-16T21:00:00-05:00" n="605" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d605">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.24 FLC/8–1748: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-08-17T11:00:00+09:00">August 17, 1948—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 17—3:38 a.m.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1523. In response to numerous inquiries we have in each case told Foreign Office
                    that question of termination date for declaration under Surplus Property
                    Agreement was under consideration in Washington, Deptel 1111, August 3. We have
                    now received formal note from Foreign Office stating matter is urgent and
                    requesting immediate designation US delegate to discuss problem. Has Department
                    information when Luboshez will return to Shanghai?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
